<TEXT>
gunmen fought pitched battles in a 
college campus and a populated neighborhood on monday and 10 people 
were killed and 34 wounded officials said 
authorities clamped an indefinite curfew in two districts where 
the clashes broke out and ordered police to shoot violators 
at least 46 people have been killed and hundreds wounded in 
shootings since may 15 authorities said 
no group has claimed responsibility for the latest wave of 
violence in hyderabad a city of 3 million in southern sind 
province but police blame a renegade faction of a militant indian 
immigrant party the mojahir qami movement 
supporters of the group which represents moslem immigrants from 
india who entered pakistan after the 1947 partition of the 
subcontinent are demanding recognition as a fifth nationality 
along with the baluch sindis pathans and punjabis 
in karachi capital of sind and pakistans largest city two 
teenagers were killed and four others injured in a shootout at a 
local college that has come to resemble an armed camp police said 
the victims of mondays shooting belonged to the peoples 
student federation the student wing of prime minister benazir 
bhuttos pakistan peoples party police said 
they said supporters of the rival all pakistan mojahir students 
organization opened fire with automatic weapons 
in another incident on monday supporters of the mojahir qami 
movement opened fire on police trying to search the house of a 
member of the group supporters of the group opened fire from their 
houses and rooftops and the battle lasted for nearly two hours 
police said 
it was unclear if mondays eight other casualties were all from 
that incident or if there were additional scattered clashes 
in the capital of islamabad opposition parties said bhuttos 
17monthold government has failed to restore lawandorder to her 
home province and asked president ghulam ishaq khan to declare a 
state of emergency 
thousands of riot police paramilitary troops and soldiers have 
been patrolling the streets of hyderabad on foot and in jeeps with 
mounted machine guns but have failed to stop the shootings 
hyderabad and the port city of karachi have been rocked in 
recent years by ethnic violence that has claimed more than 2000 
lives 
