itself that the city was one of five areas designated by national 
drug policy chief william bennett for extra federal aid 
in 1986 the deas los angeles office ranked third in the nation 
in drug arrests with 452 behind only new york with 1066 and miami 
with 861 according to dea spokesman joe keefe 
by 1989 bennett noted dea had 1033 major drug investigations 
under way in los angeles again behind only new york and miami 
