2125 million pieces of mail in the first half of fiscal 1990 
which began oct 1 projected over a full year the figures would 
be 5327 million pieces and 789 million in expenditures 
two prominent house republicans minority leader bob michel of 
illinois and bill frenzel of minnesota have introduced bills aimed 
at further limiting the number of town meeting and newsletter 
mailings establishing separate accounts for each house member and 
public disclosure 
both plan to try to add their proposals to the appropriation 
bill for running congress 
at the moment there has been no sign of help from the 
majority house democratic leadership frenzel said the frank is 
a very powerful influence in elections i dont think the democrats 
are going to let loose of it without some great pressure being 
applied 
