in the debates make it extraordinarily tough for lawmakers to make 
a dispassionate choice congress can be a very intimate place and 
the peer pressure can be so enormous that voting no is not an 
acceptable option 
of course much of what congress does is based to some degree on 
personal experiences of the members such as the former farmer who 
might get on the agriculture committee to write farm laws 
other lawmakers experiences may be translated into legislation 
of a less magnanimous nature such as a provision in a tax bill to 
help out the family business or a government project for a 
developer friend back home 
