disarming despite the high commands decision 
but sovalbarro said that simply meant individual contras 
wouldnt be stopped if they wanted to leave he said that had 
always been the case the contras are volunteers and anyone can 
leave any time 
but as leaders we cannot tell our fighters to demobilize 
until there is a guarantee that they will be left in peace 
sovalbarro said 
fighters interviewed by the ap said they would not disband 
without orders the sandinistas are doing things that arent good 
for us said a rebel who called himself bengala the bengal 
he said he had been fighting for six years 
