<TEXT>
teenage mutant turtles exist offscreen 
but they are too sick to fight crime or eat pizza 
the unhappy green sea turtles suffer from an elephant manlike 
disease called fibropapilloma that causes tumors internally and on 
their eyes mouths necks flippers jaws and tails 
some tumors get larger than a softball and often reoccur 
said dr elliot jacobson a professor of wildlife medicine at the 
university of florida they make the turtle grotesque teenage 
mutant green turtles are for real 
afflicted turtles have been found off the florida keys in the 
indian river lagoon on floridas east coast the caribbean and near 
the hawaiian islands 
in the keys the plague is so widespread that experts say 50 
percent of the endangered green sea turtles are sick or dying from 
fibropapilloma which causes them to become blind or drown 
its an epidemic among green sea turtles comparable to aids in 
humans said jacobson who is heading a yearlong research project 
fibropapilloma was first identified by marine biologists in 
1938 its cause is unknown but the strongest theory blames a virus 
possibly aggravated by water pollution jacobson said recently 
scientists are unsure how many green turtles are left in the 
world but they are considered an endangered species they feed on 
seagrass and marine plants 
between 1983 and 1989 134 green sea turtles were found dead 
jacobson said seventy had fibropapilloma hardest hit were turtles 
in the teenage stages of life 
its hard to find a turtle that is healthy and free of 
growths said tina brown a conservationist and keys charter boat 
captain 
she and richard moretti recruited jacobson to study the disease 
at the hidden harbor marine environmental project center morettis 
statelicensed marine sanctuary on key vaca where marathon is 
located 
six healthy turtles on loan to the cleveland and the toledo zoos 
were returned to florida this month to participate in the study 
five others from clearwater found to be free of fibropapilloma but 
suffering handicaps round out a study group 
the 11 turtles are being housed in an 800gallon fiberglass 
tank where they will be infected and exposed to the disease in 
hopes of finding its agent and ultimately the key to a serum 
before fibropapilloma the most serious threat to the species 
was its popularity as the main ingredient in soup in the 1950s a 
federal law was passed prohibiting the sale or import of green sea 
turtles 
teenage mutant ninja turtles are cartoon creations depicting pet 
turtles transformed into pizzaeating martial artsloving crime 
fighters they were recently introduced in liveaction form to the 
movies where they vaulted to box office success 
