a surge in income tax payments helped the 
government set a record 4252 billion budget surplus in april one 
month after a record monthly deficit the treasury department 
reported monday 
aprils receipts reduced the deficit so far for the fiscal year 
that started last oct 1 to 10834 billion down from 15085 
billion in march but still 233 percent more than the deficit at 
this time last year 
and the deficit still was more than the 100 billion target set 
by the grammrudman balanced budget law with five more months 
remaining in fiscal 1990 
the march deficit had been 5334 billion topping the previous 
record of 394 billion in may 1986 
the bush administration budget last january estimated the 1990 
deficit to be 1238 billion although officials admit it will be 
revised upward because of the unexpected costs of the savings and 
loan bailout increased interest rates and a lessthanexpected 
revenue 
the congressional budget office in march projected the deficit 
to be 159 billion 
revenues last month were up 83 percent from april 1989 to 
139624 billion while spending rose 99 percent to 97107 
billion 
the biggest previous monthly surplus was the 4057 billion of 
april 1989 
individual income tax receipts totaled 7438 billion last 
month up from 6853 billion in april 1989 corporate income taxes 
payments however fell from 1469 billion in april 1989 to 1338 
billion last month 
louis crandall chief economist for rh wrightson amp associates 
in new york said the unexpectedly large income tax receipts were 
due to payments that usually are posted in may being entered in 
aprils books 
its setting us up for a very steep may deficit he said 
revenues for the first seven months of fiscal 1990 totaled 
59792 billion up 49 percent from the same period of fiscal 
1989 spending totaled 70626 billion a 74 percent advance over 
the first seven months of the last fiscal year 
the biggest spending categories as usual were the military 
social security and other programs for the department of health and 
human services and interest on the national debt 
military spending totaled 2139 billion for the month and 
16686 billion so far this year it is projected to total 28679 
billion for the entire fiscal year 
social security payments amounted to 1887 billion for the 
month and 13824 billion for the year so far they are projected 
to total 24459 billion for the year 
other hhs programs including medicare and medicaid totaled 
1681 billion during april and 10946 billion thus far they are 
projected to total 19117 billion in fiscal 1990 
interest on the national debt amounted to 1657 billion for the 
month and 14584 billion so far this year it is projected to 
total 25485 billion for the entire year 
