<TEXT>
security forces in kashmir on monday 
opened fire on a crowd of 100000 mourners carrying the body of a 
slain moslem leader killing at least 41 people and wounding 300 
officials said 
earlier monday an official source in new delhi speaking on 
condition of anonymity gave a different account of the shooting 
he said militants opened fire on paramilitary troops and in the 
crossfire approximately 20 people were killed and 40 were 
wounded 
witnesses and doctors in srinagar said 30 bodies and at least 
300 people with bullet wounds were brought to soura hospital 
official sources in srinagar speaking on condition of anonymity 
said 41 were killed in the firing 
witnesses said about 40 bodies were still on the streets of the 
hawal neighborhood of srinagar where the shooting took place the 
city was under curfew and the reports could not be confirmed 
immediately 
prior to mondays killings nearly 400 people had been killed in 
kashmir in clashes between security forces and moslem militants 
the militants want the predominantly moslem state to secede from 
mostly hindu india 
a highranking us government delegation arrived in new delhi 
late sunday to talk with indian leaders about the kashmir crisis 
that has inflamed tensions between india and pakistan 
