gates and kelly met indian prime minister vp singh and urged 
india and pakistan to settle the issue with dialogue 
on monday srinagar the capital of kashmir was under curfew 
following the assassination of maulvi mohammad farooq kashmirs 
top islamic religious leader 
but tens of thousands of mourners defied the curfew and streamed 
to soura hospital where they took farooqs body and began marching 
in a procession to his office 6 miles away 
witnesses speaking on condition of anonymity said members of 
the paramiltary central reserve police force opened fire without 
warning on the procession at about the 5mile point 
they said farooqs coffin was hit with bullets and the body fell 
out some of the mourners put the body with fresh bullet wounds 
back into the coffin and ran with it into the narrow alleys to his 
office 
foarooqs aides said a funeral date has not been set 
