joined the call for independence after the jan 20 crackdown 
the violence in kashmir has led to a deterioration of relations 
between india and pakistan 
india accuses pakistan of arming and training the moslem 
militants pakistan denies the charge and accuses india of 
violating human rights in a bid to quash what it says is a fight 
for selfdetermination 
the dispute began in 1947 when british colonial india gained 
independence and was divided along religious lines into pakistan 
and india 
kashmirs hindu ruler chose to merge his state with india 
despite its moslem majority pakistan objected to the move and the 
dispute has led to two wars with india 
