<TEXT>
environment minister lucien bouchard prime 
minister brian mulroneys chief lieutenant in quebec resigned 
monday dealing what may be a fatal blow to the meech lake accord 
on keeping quebec in the federation 
the 1987 accord a proposed constitutional amendment would give 
provinces special powers and recognize quebec as a distinct 
society within canada all 10 provinces by law have a june 23 
deadline to ratify the accord 
the constitutional dispute over the accord has revived 
independence talk in quebec a largely frenchspeaking province 
bouchard and mulroney agreed that bouchard would quit after an 
hourlong meeting at the prime ministers residence monday sources 
told the canadian press news agency 
bouchard 52 was considered the leader of the nationalists in 
the 61member quebec conservative caucus in parliament 
other quebec nationalists are likely to view his resignation as 
rejection of a special house of commons committee report 
recommending ratification of the meech lake accord and of added 
measures contained in a companion resolution 
bouchard got in trouble after sending a telegram of 
encouragement to the parti quebecois which in 1980 fought for an 
independent quebec 
mulroney counts bouchard among his oldest and closest political 
friends 
in a telegram sent to a parti quebecois meeting in alma quebec 
bouchard praised those who fought for an independent quebec during 
the 1980 referendum 
