a federal appeals court ordered an injunction 
may 17 preventing reuters from backing out of a photoexchange 
agreement with united press international 
the 2nd us circuit court of appeals in reversing a lower 
courts decision said upi had shown that it would suffer 
irreparable harm if the arrangement were discontinued 
the request for the injunction stemmed from a counterclaim by 
upi to a reuters lawsuit that seeks to void the picture exchange 
in march us district judge peter k leisure denied the order 
and upi appealed 
three judges of the appeals court reversed leisure and directed 
him to issue the injunction which would remain in effect until the 
lawsuits are resolved 
the pictureexchange contract was made in 1984 and called for 
upi to supply reuters with photographs from the united states and 
for reuters to provide upi with pictures from other countries the 
agreement was to run for 10 years beginning in 1985 
reuters claimed the agreement is not living up to its 
expectations upi said it would lose clients and possibly go out of 
business without foreign photos from reuters 
