the bill drew widespread interest from newspaper executives 
across the country who saw it as one of the most blatant attempts 
at pressbashing in recent memory said dick shelton executive 
director of the florida press association 
we felt they legislators were peeved at the press and wanted 
to get the press attention shelton said i think the 
