public works director joe guerra was damaged in the first of four 
times articles about a candidates claim that city equipment was 
used improperly 
but the jury awarded no damages holding that the offending 
article did not constitute actual malice nor did the newspaper 
act with reckless disregard for the truth the jury said 
guerra felix de leon and guadalupe f gonzalez sued the times 
and one of its editors in connection with articles published oct 
1720 1985 
the jury found that all four articles were substantially true 
and the subject was of public concern 
the times contended that the first article merely reported what 
