clean up after itself when it errs he said 
riley said most of the registers staff treat the matter 
professionally we criticize everybody else in the world and i 
think the staff though theyre not always pleased realizes we 
have to be subject to the same criticism he said 
the ombudsmen agreed there are some issues such as abortion on 
which they have no easy answers mcnulty said he gets about the 
same number of complaints from prolife advocates as from 
prochoice advocates claiming a story was biased against them 
we listen but at the same time we dont let those criticisms 
dampen or curtail our coverage we still consider ourselves news 
people we will still cover the stories riley said 
there are no solutions to some complaints about stories but 
what is important is that there is a twoway communication between 
the reader and the newspaper with that comes the hope that the 
paper is hearing what the reader is saying mcnulty said 
</TEXT>
