its been 15 years since the fall of saigon and 
still the movies about the war keep coming 
most are bad a few are firstrate and some are wellintended 
efforts that just dont hit the mark 
the last would best describe last flight out an nbc movie 
based on the real story of the last refugeepacked pan american 
flight out of saigon six days before the fall of the city and south 
vietnam to north vietnamese forces 
it stars richard crenna as pan am pilot dan hood and james earl 
jones as al topping the airlines saigon station manager two men 
who exist and who defied the rules in a good cause in the panicky 
days near the end of the war 
