<TEXT>
 
editors note the days of wine and roses and hostesses with 
the mostest have departed the washington scene reading george 
bushs lips capital social life is texmex flicks and popcorn on 
the side 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
after the hollywood glitz of the reagan years 
the washington social scene under george bush seems as flat as last 
nights champagne and as boring as the last guest to leave the 
party 
blacktie parties for jetsetting glitterati from beverly hills 
have given way to folksy barbecues at camp david and cozy evenings 
of popcorn and movies at the white house for a few close friends 
jelly beans are out texmex junk food is in leave the bill 
blass gown in the closet and grab a ralph lauren sweater for 
kennebunkport scratch that candlelit soiree in georgetown the 
presidents heading for the horseshoe pit 
the social whirl in short is gurgling down the drain 
what social scene asks robin weir former hairdresser to 
nancy reagan and her california friends 
bemoaning the decline in star quality of his salons clientele 
weir sniffed weve gone from betsy bloomingdale to roseanne 
barr 
jayne ikard wife of a former texas congressman and a fixture on 
the local party circuit for 20 years says her waistline tells the 
story 
lets just say i gained 8 pounds during the first month of the 
reagan administration and this year im staying on an even keel 
im not gaining and im not losing 
no one is complaining about george and barbara bush who are 
popular and energetic hosts but times have changed the reagans 
are basking in the golden west and the grande dames of society 
have gone the way of dance cards and white gloves the nights 
belong to the nouveau riche whose ideas of fun is throwing a 
charity ball 
when bush took office everyone eagerly awaited the emergence of 
georgette mosbacher wife of commerce secretary robert mosbacher 
as washingtons hostess with the mostest 
but mrs mosbacher perhaps wary of dipping her toe in the shark 
pool stayed in new york to run her cosmetics business the other 
prime candidate penne korth a bush pal from texas who cochaired 
his inaugural shipped out as ambassador to mauritius 
its as though somebody unplugged the jacuzzi and we were all 
sitting there wet and waiting for the action to start said 
society columnist diana mclellan the whole feeling of the city 
has changed enormously 
whats different is that the epicenter of the capitals social 
life has shifted to the white house where the gregarious 
funloving bushes are setting the pace with their own parties 
receptions and yall come on over evenings with family and old 
friends 
the bushes know everybody said mrs mclellan theyve 
been here a long time and they know all the players mrs ikard 
compares capital society under the reagans and the bushes by 
saying its the difference between a flirtation and courtship 
and a stable happy marriage 
says gretchen poston former social secretary under president 
carter this is a very serious white house and theyre not going 
out to dinner parties like the reagans the bushes focus is on the 
home 
its a far cry from 1981 when the reagans came to town with a 
galaxy of social luminaries the walter annenbergs william french 
smiths caspar weinbergers charles z wicks to excite the most 
jaded partygoers 
bush an old washington hand ushered in the 90s with a cabinet 
full of old familiar faces his idea of a surprise was john 
sununu the white house chief of staff and former new hampshire 
governor who is something less than a party animal 
john who not even the social sets pricey facelifts could hide 
the frowns of dismay 
the bushes are wellliked and they entertain in a warm 
gracious manner says barbara gamarekian of the new york times 
but washington feeds on new faces and personalities and after 
eight years of the reagans people got tired of guest lists with 
the same names over and over again 
everyone was looking for a change and they didnt get it 
she said 
in truth washington has grown up urban sprawl is rampant 
traffic is getting impossible distant cow pastures have been 
bulldozed for milliondollar mansions tiffany the jewel of new 
yorks fifth avenue has branched into a suburban virginia shopping 
mall 
long gone is the sleepy southern town where the oldmoney 
doyennes of high society entertained a small circle of friends at 
lavish dinner parties sprinkled with senators cabinet members 
diplomats and olympian newspaper pundits 
nobody has filled the vacuum left by the late perle mesta and 
gwendolyn cafritz the legendary washington hostesses who made 
headlines by catering to the powerful todays careerminded 
congressional and cabinet wives show little interest in playing the 
hostess game 
the reason things are so dull is that nobody has come to town 
with the ambition to rise above the crowd and fill that role 
said society watcher charlotte hays of the washington times 
the hottest invitation in town these days arrives in a white 
house envelope or in a casual telephone call from george or 
barbara bush 
everyone wants to be on the guest list for those very small 
very intimate parties that the bushes give every month or so he 
said they invite about 30 people over for a light buffet supper 
and a movie theres almost a family feeling with the bushes 
walking around greeting each guest 
those invited represent an eclectic mix of society figures 
corporate executives political insiders bush children old texas 
friends a few media types and an occasional celebrity 
the bush circle seems endlessly expansive there is no bush 
clique it just seems to go on and on said mrs ikard who was 
a guest at bushs recent state dinner for venezuelan president 
carlos andres perez 
mrs ikard recalls past presidents who shunned outsiders 
the carters had their inner circle of georgians the reagans 
had the californians and never invited anyone up to the family 
quarters on the third floor camelot was strictly for the kennedy 
people either you were in or you were out she said 
bush doesnt seem to have an a list of social favorites that 
appear regularly on white house guest lists but his inner circle 
if there is one probably would include such unfamiliar names as 
russell train john e chapoton fred zeder and dean burch 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> AP900521-0207 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
train is chairman of the world wildlife fund chapoton is a 
washington lawyer and former chief tax official at the reagan 
treasury zeder is chairman of the overseas private investment 
corp burch is director general of intelsat and a former republican 
speechwriter 
bush delights in asking outoftown guests to spend the night at 
the white house if a party is running late he sometimes takes a 
snapshot of them lying on lincolns bed 
among those who have taken toothbrushes and pajamas upstairs in 
the bush white house are kentucky horse breeder will farish 
hollywood producer jerry weintraub and baine kerr executive 
committee chairman of pennzoil 
old bush friend jack steele of houston was so awed during his 
sleepover in the lincoln bedroom that he stayed up gazing at the 
washington monument and writing notes at the desk where lincoln 
signed the emancipation proclamation 
bush also actively courts the friendship of show business 
celebrities recent guests at the white house or camp david have 
included muscleman and actor arnold schwarzenegger and entertainer 
michael jackson 
a devoted fan of country music and the movies bush invited 
jimmy dean and the gatlin brothers to join him as weekend guests 
for a screening of coupe de ville at the presidential retreat 
in the catoctin mountains of western maryland 
the presidents movie fare is as diverse as his choice of 
friends in recent months while scooping up handfuls of popcorn 
from silver bowls he has seen scandal field of dreams 
the hunt for red october the fabulous baker boys naked 
gun and stella as well as oscar winner driving miss 
daisy and nominees glory and my left foot 
bush is no stayathome however 
he likes to dash out of the white house to buy fresh bagels at 
wagshalls a local delicatessen or make an impromptu appearance 
at the kennedy center for some light stage entertainment for their 
45th wedding anniversary on jan 6 the bushes went there to see 
a tuna christmas a smalltown texas comedy 
bush enjoys gathering family and friends for an evening of gusty 
dining at local restaurants including galileos an italian 
restaurant near dupont circle and the bustling rio grande cafe in 
suburban bethesda md which serves texmex specialties 
intimates say the president also favors the peking gourmet inn 
in suburban fairfax county va where bush indulges the taste for 
chinese delicacies that he acquired as chief of the us liaison 
office in beijing in the 1970s 
among his favorite dining companions is vic gold longtime press 
spokesman and speechwriter for republican biggies and coauthor of 
bushs autobiography looking forward gold recently introduced 
bush to i ricchi a swank local tuscan restaurant 
when the bushes moved in says gold they made a rule they 
wouldnt be prisoners of the white house or alter their outgoing 
gregarious style of entertaining 
when its party time around town bush administration bigwigs 
are simply staying away embassy row has been quiet since the days 
when argentinas alejandro orfila and the dashing iranian 
ambassador ardeshir zahedi were the toast of the town 
these cabinet people have been here before and they have 
their own friendships said socialite buffy cafritz people 
like jack kemp and dick cheney are a very hardworking group ill 
tell you theyre always at their desks 
mrs cafritz sees washington scaling down in the 1990s to small 
intimate dinner parties corporate lobbyists are bankrolling the 
big blacktie blowouts that once were the specialty of the citys 
grande dames and fundraising benefits from aids charities to 
opera balls are proliferating 
my mail is half junk mail and half invitations to benefits 
sighed mrs ikard 
when reagan was here everyone was upscale and la glamour 
or pretending to be says craig stoltz editor of dossier 
magazine tip sheet of the social set now people are affecting a 
commitment to issues and causes with a lot of selfcongratulating 
you hear more talk about values than at k mart on a saturday 
afternoon 
mrs mosbachers low profile has been a major disappointment 
says stoltz at the democratic convention everyone said where 
was george now theyre asking where is georgette shes 
apparently absorbing the quieter gentler tone of the bush years 
said hairdresser robin weir georgette finally gave a party 
the other night and her guests had to write a check to a charitable 
cause to go its all social conscience now if you want to come 
to my house youve gotta pay 
virtually unknown among the new power players on the washington 
social scene is the elitist membership of three highly secretive 
allmale social clubs to which bush belongs the bohemian club in 
san francisco and the alfalfa and alibi clubs in washington 
the alibi in fact is so clandestine that its members wont 
even acknowledge that it exists but it is known that all three 
serve primarily to give prominent public figures the chance to shed 
their inhibitions and enjoy eating drinking and swapping funny 
stories without fear of disclosure 
in a recent column for washingtonian magazine diana mclellan 
wrote that the most precisely calibrated gauge of status in the 
city is the seating at opening nights at the national theater 
if thats true then alma viator must be the ultimate authority 
on the ins and outs of bushs washington as the theaters public 
relations director she makes seating decisions for opening night 
ms viator who also is a freelance consultant on throwing 
successful washington parties says nobody beats the president of 
course as the prize catch of the evening ditto for secretary of 
state james a baker or secretary mosbacher if bush sends regrets 
and dont forget house speaker tom foley 
other names high on her list include katharine graham chairman 
of the washington post co pat kluge estranged wife of broadcast 
baron john kluge media heavyweights like ted koppel or roger mudd 
and headlinemaking diplomats like soviet ambassador yuri dubinin 
she tries to nab sort of sexy senators like john kerry of 
massachusetts alan simpson of wyoming or bill bradley of new 
jersey plus anyone whos ever run for president even if he lost 
throw in a couple of movie stars for excitement she says for 
added spice include some people whove gotten into a little 
trouble like former reagan white house aides michael j deaver 
or robert mcfarlane 
other big names include public relations honcho robert gray 
playwright larry l king actress lynda carter and the enduring 
buffy cafritz and then theres former house speaker thomas p 
oneill whos still a huge draw at a washington party even 
though he spends his retirement popping out of suitcases on tv 
commercials 
tip has no power nothing said ms viator but he has 
such a great personality hes still very much loved 
</TEXT>
