editors note nowhere do celebrity stars shine brighter than 
along the heavenly california beach named malibu but tuesday they 
will pause in their orbits to vote about such earthly matters as 
secession and sewage 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
latvia lithuania and estonia yearn for 
independence from the soviet union staten island wants to secede 
from new york city not all that long ago new york city wanted to 
secede from new york state 
so far nothing in politics there is no such thing as nofault 
divorce 
but tuesday the 20000 residents of this spangled coastal 
community everyone from andrews julie to zimbalist efrem 
put their local political future on the line about half of them 
those who are eligible to go to the polls can declare their desire 
to secede from los angeles county and become a city in charge of 
its own future 
similar independence movements have become a wavelet along the 
golden strand from la to san diego 
its been a 26year offandon battle cityhood supporters 
thwarted over and over again from gaining selfdetermination 
for over two years the county board of supervisors has 
repeatedly blocked the way to the polls this year superior court 
judge dzintra janavs ordered them to stand aside 
the county wanted to delay the vote a year pleading bureacratic 
adjustments when that was taken to the same superior court judge 
the county removed her and installed a new judge but alas that 
judge ruled the year delay unnecessary 
in malibu they were wearing tshirts that asked whats the 
difference between malibu and the united states in the united 
states you can vote 
cityhood seems to have a real chance at last 
it inspired president george bush in a beverly hills speech to 
say 
people from panama to prague are striving for democracy 
selfdetermination is contagious they even want it in malibu i 
understand leaping over volleyball nets to freedom 
which brings in a third player in the freedom game 
pepperdine university high on a splendiferous hill overlooking 
the pacific and known on national television for fielding 
extravagantly talented volleyball teams has already gone to other 
state authorities for permission to be captain of its fate master 
of its sewage 
sewage believe it or not is the key word 
like the grand canyon malibu must be seen to be appreciated it 
stretches 26 miles along the charmed california coast north of 
santa monica and the pacific palisades both evidence of what 
unencumbered development can do where houses were built on eroding 
sand bluffs in an effort to catch the ocean view 
burning red sunsets over the pacific the high light catching 
the mountains become so commonplace to residents they barely take 
notice they do notice that on a clear day they can see santa 
catalina island 23 miles out 
in their book backroom politics authors bill and nancy 
boyarsky wrote of the long sewer battle 
one of the few communities that has learned to understand this 
obscure political game is malibu in southern california where the 
santa monica mountains reach the sea there the canyons widen into 
coastal plain and then become part of the beaches 
malibu is almost 30 miles from downtown los angeles and even 
today it still has a bit of a rural look but only a little just 
a few feet separate houses on the beach and during rush hour and 
on weekends the pacific coast highway which runs through malibu 
is a noisy smelly tangle of recreational vans sports cars camper 
trucks and sedans 
the desire to develop malibu has not diminished there is 
still vacant land and the only thing stopping a building boom 
along the beach and back into the mountains is the lack of sewers 
