<TEXT>
 
fire birds touchstone pictures rated pg13 
 
a sure sign that a movie is doomed from the start is when it 
opens with a printed quote from president bushs september 1989 
socalled war on colombian drug lords and the screening 
audience giggles 
fire birds tumbles to the very depths of lousy filmmaking on 
that note 
with a stilted screenplay by nick thiel and paul f edwards 
story by step tyner john k swenson and dale dye that never 
quite figures out if its a silly love story or a contrived 
adventure fire birds just might be a poor attempt at hollywood 
patriotism 
jake preston nicolas cage and billie lee guthrie sean young 
are part of an elite army helicopter corps being trained for a 
secret invasion in south america their expert mentor is brad 
little tommy lee jones 
training is partly through computerized simulators which make 
video games look wimpy and actual flight maneuvers the shots 
whether computerized or real are breathtaking and provide the 
only real excitement in the movie 
jake in muhammad ali bravura reminds anyone wholl listen that 
hes the greatest and next to little he is guthrie will 
remind anyone wholl listen that shes no longer romantically 
interested in jake who stalks her like a greedy ivory poacher 
