<TEXT>
the whitney musuem of american art will present a retrospective 
of the entire career of maurice prendergast one of the leading 
figures in the development of american modernism in the early 20th 
century 
prendergast who was born in newfoundland in 1858 did not 
receive formal art training until 1891 when he spent a brief time 
at the academie julian in paris 
he studied cezanne whistler and the nabis painters and was the 
first american to return from europe who assimilated 
postimpressionist styles in his work 
the whitney exhibit is grouped la belle epoque observations 
of modern life 18911906 early modernism studies in color 
and form 19071913 personal vision myth fantasy and the 
idyll 19141924 
the retrospective opens june 1 and runs through sept 2 
here is a list of exhibits and shows at other galleries and 
museums in the united states 
