<TEXT>
charlton heston doesnt think he got the part 
of moses all by himself in cecil b demilles epic the ten 
commandments 
i think michaelangelo got me the part he says 
the 1956 classic is back in the news as part of its film 
preservation program paramount pictures has restored prints in 
70mm with sixtrack stereo sound the ten commandments was 
shown at two los angeles theaters on may 1624 with engagements to 
follow across the country 
at his coldwater canyon home heston recalled his dealings with 
demille the ultimate autocrat of the movie set 
demilles casting method was very curious said the actor 
who had starred for the director in the greatest show on earth 
you never got to read the script nobody did he would tell 
you the story of the film from the point of view of your character 
he would tell you the various scenes and he already had designs 
for the props and sets and costumes he would show you all these 
things but he never would say i am considering you for this 
part 
so you couldnt say id really like to play that part and 
it would be marvelous to have it all you could say was it 
certainly sounds like its going to be a marvelous picture mr 
demille 
then two or three months later he would call you in and it 
would be essentially the same thing though he had more things to 
show you finally he made a choice but you were never engaged in 
a dialogue on that score heston said 
i think the thing he could never get out of his mind was that 
early in the casting process someone pointed out that 
michaelangelos statue of moses looked very much like me it really 
does the broken nose is the same the cheekbones the long jaw 
the forehead the deepset eyes and all that 
paramounts restoration and rerelease of its classics the 
first was funny face drew applause from heston long involved 
with the american film institute he has been vitally interested in 
preservation the most important thing the afi does 
if restoration doesnt take place then the film is gone 
he said that would be tragic because film has been described 
not only as the art form of the 20th century but the american art 
form 
paramount is taking a significant lead in the archival 
process behind what used to be the paramount tank with the big sky 
cyclorama a curved screen used as background for stage settings 
in back where many of the scenes for the ten commandments were 
shot the studio is building an archival facility it will be used 
to store films under controlled conditions of climate and 
humidity 
illinoisborn charlton heston was a 27yearold actor from 
broadway and television when he arrived in hollywood for a 
fivepicture contract with hal wallis his first movie was dark 
city his second film was the greatest show on earth which 
he says brought his best notice ever 
demille showed him a letter from a moviegoer who complimented 
james stewart betty hutton gloria grahame cornel wilde and the 
rest of the cast adding i thought the circus manager did very 
well in there with the real actors 
heston appeared in a few more films until demille summoned him 
once more moses was an immense role for an actor barely in his 30s 
i think in all there were nine different makeups said 
heston not counting the baby which my son fraser played at 
the age of 3 months i went from the young prince moses to the aged 
patriarch the whitehaired longbearded moses who watches his 
people cross over jordan and he goes up the mountain not to 
immortality because he wasnt divine but he disappears from the 
ken of man 
what was it like working for demille 
he was very demanding and mind you i only worked for him in 
his last two pictures if he was a martinet in his early days that 
had mellowed a bit he was relentlessly demanding so was willy 
wyler so was george stevens 
he was extraordinarily courteous with the actors he had quite 
a formal manner he still came to work in a suit and a tie on 
location the same suit with britches and puttees for rough country 
he didnt shoot a lot of closeups in those days they didnt 
look at casablanca and there are three closeups in the entire 
film two of bergman and one of bogart the proliferation of 
closeups has increased as the film definition and color gradation 
has improved 
heston added that demille often used assistant directors and 
prop men as whipping boys but was always courteous to extras 
addressing them as ladies and gentlemen 
chuck heston at 67 has weathered the years well hes never 
dodged a controversy such as his battles with the liberal ed 
asner over screen actors guild politics ads for the national rifle 
association and his support of president bush and other republicans 
and hes kept his hand in the profession he recently starred in 
treasure island written and directed by fraser and released on 
the tnt network heston reported proudly that the movie was picked 
up by warner bros for theatrical distribution 
another new film is solar crisis a sciencefiction tale for 
release this summer he has produced his second book reporting on 
his experience in directing the caine mutiny court martial in 
china most recently he was promoted to god playing the diety in 
paul hogans new film almost an angel 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

