of the egg 
ramon de la mata urban policy consultant to the government of 
the autonomous region of madrid which commissioned the project 
recently talked about the 71yearold saenzs de oizas perspective 
in an interview 
confronted with an aggressive environment the adjacent 
trafficclogged m30 beltway and surrounding faceless apartment 
blocks oiza builds a wall around his houses saying i dont 
like this city lets turn this building in on itself 
pozo del huevo is one of numerous shantytowns built in the 1950s 
on the outskirts of madrid by rural immigrants drawn to the city by 
an industrial boom land speculation and inadequate provisions for 
public dwellings condemned them and their children to substandard 
housing in areas that have become breeding grounds for delinquency 
and drug trafficking 
oizas rejection of the urban environment through his walled 
city is felt as a snub to the residents of the prosperous adjacent 
la estrella neighborhood and the surrounding area of moratalaz 
where prices for threebedroom apartments have almost doubled since 
1987 
their damaged pride surfaced as raw fury when they learned it 
would be the inhabitants of the pozo del huevo shantytown in 
their eyes all gypsies drug addicts and carriers of switchblade 
knives who would be moving into the project 
a lot of people talk about preventive medicine these days 
said local resident and hospital employee juan domingo well 
what we want to do is prevent a crime wave around here 
as madrids sensationalist press fueled the fires with such 
headlines as the human cage and prison for the poor 
residents of la estrella and moratalaz cut traffic on the m30 
every thursday afternoon demanding that the pozo del huevo people 
be housed elsewhere and the saenz de oiza apartments be sold to 
people such as themselves 
some 65 percent of the adult males in the pozo del huevo are 
seasonal construction workers and as in most urban areas of spain 
youth umemployment is more than double the 16 percent overall 
national rate 
but heroin addiction and trafficking endemic in most of 
madrids other marginal areas and the accompanying high crime 
levels are negligible 
we drove the dealers out at gunpoint says tomas blazquez 
president of the pozo del huevo neighborhood association 
maria luisa who lives with her husband two children and 
parentsinlaw in one of the damp ramshackle shanties in pozo del 
huevo says there is concealed homelessness in madrid 
nobody dares to build shanty houses anymore twenty years ago 
you got married young and if you didnt have a house you built a 
shanty now young people carry on living with their parents in 
their shanties 
but urban affairs officials say shantybuilding on the fringes 
of madrid however illegal is still very active 
housing relocation head rosa molina says gypsies who live in the 
la veguilla shantytown north of the city are now building shanties 
for moroccans the most recent of the immigrant arrivals and 
renting them for the equivalent of 100 a month 
another housing official miguel angel pascual say this 
shanty speculation is being fueled by the massive influx into 
the madrid area by families attracted by news of government plans 
to build extensive lowcost housing 
when the government council member for urban policy urged that 
the 186 million saenz de oiza project apartments be sold to 
middleclass families to finance other housing for pozo del huevo 
people somewhere else they marched on government headquarters 
demanding respect for the 1985 agreement they also expressed 
resentment that the architect and builders failed to solicit their 
opinion about their new residence 
a day later the madrid regional government renewed its 
commitment to move the people of the egg well from their crumbling 
shanties into the walled city 
