<TEXT>
here are some facts and figures about the united 
auto workers union 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
membership about 1 million active and 400000 retirees in the 
united states now down from about 15 million active and 300000 
retirees in 1979 
membership breakdown 68 percent in automobile and autoparts 
industries 7 percent in the aerospace industry 6 percent in 
agricultural implements and about 20 percent in a variety of other 
jobs including some brewery workers state employees in michigan 
and jai alai players in new england 
locals about 1200 all in the united states except local 251 
in wallaceburg ontario 
bargaining units about 3200 some locals have more than one 
bargaining unit 
contracts current labor agreements with general motors corp 
and ford motor co were negotiated and signed in 1987 the 
uawchrysler corp contract was signed a year later all expire at 
midnight sept 14 
headquarters solidarity house in detroit 
leadership owen bieber first elected at 1983 constitutional 
convention vice presidents stephen yokich ernie lofton stan 
marshall and odessa kommer 
organization the union is governed by a 23member international 
executive board made up of seven officers and 16 regional directors 
history chartered by the american federation of labor in august 
1935 the union grew quickly after a series of sitdown strikes 
starting at gm plants in flint in early 1937 uaw members returned 
to work after a onepage contract was signed 
workers at chrysler and later ford voted to be represented by 
the union since its founding the uaw has remained free of 
widespread scandal and corruption that have plagued other large 
labor organizations 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

