soybean futures prices fell sharply monday on the chicago board 
of trade continuing a recent trend linked to weather conditions 
and greater availability of south american supplies 
grain futures also retreated in chicago on other commodity 
markets energy futures tumbled precious metals were mixed and 
livestock and meat futures were mixed 
soybean futures settled 10 cents 11 cents lower with the 
contract for delivery in july at 610 a bushel 
wheat futures ended 2 cents to 3 cents lower with july at 337 
a bushel may corn was 4 cents to 5 cents lower with july at 
277 a bushel oats were 2 cents to 3 cents lower with july at 
